0141|- [HelpText]
0142|*The current data path is shown at the end of the header line of
0143|*the Survo main window. Thus all files on this path can be referred to
0144|*simply by their names without a path designation.
0146|*The data path can be changed by the CD command and it may be changed
0147|*automatically during the Survo session when the user makes selections
0148|*from various menus, etc.
0150|*When the data path is on the system path of Survo, the part of the
0151|*system path is designated simply as <Survo>. It is strongly recommended
S   |                                     <     >
0152|*that the user creates for his/her tasks own data paths which are
0153|*not on the <Survo> path. The <Survo> path is used by the Survo programs,
S   |            <     >           <     >
0154|*other system files, and demo files.
0155|*Thus notation <Survo> can be used only in certain basic and technical
S   |               <     >
0156|*commands of Survo.
