0170|- [HelpText]
0171|*CD <path designation>
S   |    <                >
0172|*selects the data path. By default all operations of Survo use this path.
0173|*The current choice is displayed on the header line of the edit field.
0174|*If the given path does not exist, an error message is displayed.
0175|*The OS default disk and directory are changed accordingly. This helps
0176|*giving OS commands from Survo, as no pathnames need to be specified.
0177|*If no path is given, the default data path, given by the system parameter
0178|- shadow %: [LINK(q0b_10.html)] [/LINK]
0179|*'edisk', is used. (See also SYSTEM?).
S   |                             %%%%%%
0180|*DISK <path designation>
S   |      <                >
0181|*also selects the data path, but does not change the OS path. This was the
0182|*original setting in Survo: the OS default path was the same as the system
0183|*path (e.g. C:\E) all the time. Since v.5.00, and the desktop operations
0184|- shadow %: [LINK(qkv0_01.html)] [/LINK]
0185|*(see DESKTOP?), this has been changed to allow easier reference to files by
S   |      %%%%%%%
0186|*OS commands without specifying the pathnames, for example. To keep using of
0187|*the system coherent, only either one of DISK and CD can be used. Now CD is
0188|*used instead of DISK in all sucro tools of the system, so its usage is
0189|*strongly recommended. DISK is considered obsolete, but it may be needed in
0190|*some special applications.
