0202|- [HelpText]
0203|*Another way to select the data path is to press the F4:DISK key as many times
0204|*as needed. A special list of alternatives can be defined by setting system
0205|*parameters 'last_disk' and 'paths'. 'Z' as 'last_disk' implies that the
0206|*selection given by 'paths' should be used when DISK is pressed. For example,
0207|*'paths=C:\MYDATA\,C:\E\D\,D:\DAT2\,A:' . The DISK key can be disabled by
0208|*setting 'last_disk=Z:' with no 'paths' at all.
0210|*Without 'last_disk=Z:' the DISK key gives the standard alternatives, say,
0211|*A:, B:, C:\E\D\, D: in turn on the header line. (In this particular case
0212|*the paths are changed by DISK, not by CD as above.)
0214|*There are plenty of other ways to change paths. For example, the desktop
0215|*operations DD, INDEX and TREE do that. By organizing jobs to dynamic menus
0216|*using the V-sucro, paths are changed automatically by one keystroke. See:
0217|*/V ?
