0290|- [HelpText]
0291|*VARS=<list of variables>
S   |      <                 >
0292|*is a specification which selects the variables into statistical analysis.
0293|*Another way to do that is to use a MASK specification, but VARS always
0294|*overrides MASK and permanent activation status in the data file.
0295|*For example,
0296|*VARS=Height,Weight,Test1
0297|*selects the variables Height,Weight and Test1 which all are activated
0298|*by 'A' in the current data file; other variables will be passive.
0299|*VARS=ALL means that all variables are to be selected.
0300|*VARS=ALL,-Name,-Test1 means that all variables except Name and Test1 are
0301|*to be selected.
0302|*The task of each variable can be given in parentheses in the VARS list.
0303|*For example, in the LINREG operation
0304|*VARS=Height(X),Weight(X),Test1(Y),Residual(R)
0305|*selects the variables and indicates their roles in the analysis as well.
0307|*The influence of VARS is only temporary and does not change the
0308|*activation status in the data file.
