0320|- [HelpText]
0321|*MASK without parameters is an operation which leads to the activation
0322|*procedure for the fields of any Survo data file. (Another way to
0323|*start the selection and activation procedure is to press key FILE_ACT, but
0324|*this does not update any MASK line in the edit field.)
0326|*After return from MASK procedure to normal edit mode the current
0327|*line will contain a MASK specification of the form
0328|*MASK=--XX-A-YX-R---AA- (for example)
0329|*indicating the activated fields in the current data file.
0330|*If a MASK specification appears in the current subfield,
0331|*when a statistical operation like CORR,LINREG,TAB etc. is activated,
0332|*it determines the roles of the variables in the analysis.
0333|*However, a possible VARS specification always overrides MASK in
0334|- shadow %: [LINK(q03_12.html)] [/LINK]
0335|*statistical operations (See VARS?).
S   |                             %%%%
0337|*By activation of a MASK line with a given mask string (MASK=--XX-A-- ,
0338|*for example) the selection of the fields determined by that string will
0339|*be shown for a selected file and this selection may be adjusted. After
0340|*return to edit mode again the MASK line will show the latest selection.
0342|*Since a data file can contain several optional mask columns (default
0343|*number is 7), any of them can be used to indicate the selected vari-
0344|*ables by giving its number #1,#2,#3,,, as MASK=#7.
0345|*A partial selection according to a mask column is also possible. For
0346|*example, MASK=#7(XY) selects the fields indicated by X or Y in mask
0347|*column 7.
0348|*Activation of a MASK line of this type will lead to a file activation
0349|*display of that mask column for additional changes.
