0502|- [HelpText]
0503|*Survopoint display mode:
0504|*To enliven the display in the main window of Survo, variable text
0505|*may be shown on selected "Survopoint" lines.
0506|*The contents of Survopoint lines are varying either systematically
0507|*or randomly according to information given in the current edit field,
0508|*typically outside the current window.
0509|*Example:
0510|*  11 *
0511|*  12 ~ (The contents of this line will be alternating)       ~a
0512|*  13 *
0513|*  14 a 20 3 S
0514|*  15 * This is the first alternative.
0515|*  16 * Here is the second alternative.
0516|*  17 * The third alternative is here.
0518|*Please load this text into the edit field and remove leading characters
0519|*so that control characters are those shown above.
0520|*If you then press keys F1 and A, the text on line having '~' in its
0521|*control column will be changing systematically between the three
0522|*alternatives. The key combination F1 a interrupts this display mode.
0524|*In the previous example, the only Survopoint line was
0525|*  12 ~ (The contents of this line will be alternating)       ~a
0526|*The marking ~a at the end of the line tells that the rule how this
0527|*line alternates is given on a line having 'a' in its control column.
0528|*The 'a' line was
0529|*  14 a 20 3 S
0530|*and there 20 gives the time interval between changes, 3 is the number
0531|*of alternatives, and 'S' indicates that the line is changed
0532|*systematically.
0534|*Actually in the Survopoint display mode no line is moved in the edit
0535|*field. Since the line to be displayed is always referred to by a pointer
0536|*variable, merely pointers are updated and so this mode consumes very
0537|*little computer power.
0539|*In one edit field, 26 alternating lines may exist simultaneously.
0540|*Each of them is indicated (by default) by a '~' in the control column
0541|*and a marking ~x at the end of the line where x is one of the lowercase
0542|*characters from 'a' to 'z'.
0544|*Various options for the rule of alternating are
0545|*Systematic:
0546|*<time> <# of alternatives> S
S   | <    > <                 >
0547|*Uniformly random:
0548|*<time> <# of alternatives> U
S   | <    > <                 >
0549|*Random by given probabilities:
0550|*<time> <# of alternatives> p1 p2 p3 ...
S   | <    > <                 >
0551|*where p1+p2+p3+...=1
0553|*The <time> parameter is an integer telling that the change takes place
S   |     <    >
0554|*just once in <time> consecutive refreshments of the Survo main window.
S   |              <    >
0555|*The refresh rate (in this display mode only) is given by the system
0556|*parameter Survopoint_disp in SURVO.APU and it is 50 ms by default.
0557|*The default control character '~' for Survopoint lines can be changed
0558|*by the system parameter Survopoint.
0559|*A mishmash collection of several simultaneus Survopoint lines is found
0560|*by activating
0561|*LOAD <Survo>\U\D\SPOINT
S   |      <     >
